Process Table (Main Section)

PID → Process ID
USER → Owner of process
PR → Priority
NI → Nice value (priority adjustment)
VIRT → Virtual memory used
RES → Physical RAM used
SHR → Shared memory
S → Process state (R, S, Z, etc.)
%CPU → CPU usage
%MEM → Memory usage
TIME+ → Total CPU time consumed
COMMAND → Process name
================================================

Process States (Very Important) RSDTZI

R → Running
S → Sleeping
D → Uninterruptible (mostly I/O wait)
T → Stopped
Z → Zombie
I → Idle
===============================================

High load avg + high CPU → CPU bottleneck
High wa (wait) → disk issue
High memory + swap used → memory pressure
Zombie processes → parent not cleaning child

